1.title: You Better Bring It!
1.plot: The Dancing Dolls dance team prepares to compete against a fierce rival in Chattanooga, TN. Head coach, Dianna, forbids a number of dancers from participating at the event after less-than-perfect performances at rehearsal and team captain, Kayla, struggles with the added pressure of performing a solo. Meanwhile, Rittany, one of the dancers' moms, butts heads with Dianna and threatens to pull her daughter from the team.

2.title: Battle in Memphis
2.plot: The Dancing Dolls challenge their rivals, the Divas of Olive Branch, to a no-holds-barred "Street Battle", to settle once and for all which dance team is the best. The event soon gets out of hand, however, when tension on the dance floor sparks a clash between dancers and spectators. Meanwhile, Camryn gets a chance to lead the Dancing Dolls during a parade and show Miss Dianna that she has what it takes to be captain.

3.title: The Wig Is Off
3.plot: After getting cheated the week before, the Dancing Dolls return to Memphis looking for payback and are determined to beat one of their biggest rivals, the Prancing Tigerettes. Sunjai learns a hard lesson about what it takes to make the stand battle crew and her mother, Selena, learns a lesson of her own when she tries to bully Dianna. Meanwhile, Camryn gets a chance to perform her very first solo at competition.

4.title: Baby Doll Don't Mean Baby
4.plot: After losing Stand Battle two weeks in a row, the Dancing Dolls enlist their pint-sized counterparts, the Baby Dancing Dolls, to compete in their place so they can focus on developing a secret weapon to defeat their biggest rivals, The Prancing Tigerettes. Meanwhile, Selena's bad behavior threatens her daughter, Sunjai's, future on the team. And team captain, Kayla, feels the pressure as her teammates begin to question her leadership.

5.title: Sunjai in Stilettos
5.plot: The Dancing Dolls head back to Memphis to compete against two fierce rivals, the Prancing Tigerettes and the Divas of Olive Branch. Meanwhile, Sunjai earns a spot front and center in the team's Michael Jackson-inspired performance and Kayla finally asks her father to attend one of her performances.

6.title: Street Battle
6.plot: The three suspended potential captains have only week left to earn their way back into Coach D's good graces. An EPIC showdown emerges between Coach D and a DDP, when an important Dollhouse rule is broken. Meanwhile, Faith and DDP Dana take a trip to Atlanta to explore future acting and singing opportunities.

7.title: Shut Up and Dance
7.plot: The Dancing Dolls prepare to defend their title of "The Best Dance Team in Jackson" in a huge hometown battle against local rivals, the Purple Diamonds. Extremely cold weather motivates Mimi to try to convince Dianna to let the Moms back into the dance studio during rehearsal. And Sunjai gets a chance to compete in Stand Battle for the very first time.

8.title: The Lock-In
8.plot: The Dancing Dolls struggle to master difficult stands as they prepare to battle the rival team Dynamic Diamond Dollz in a Memphis competition. Dianna calls for an all-night rehearsal at the Dollhouse Dance Factory. Meanwhile, Sunjai shines in the Burlesque routine.

9.title: The Finale: Battle Royale
9.plot: Miss D and the Dancing Dolls finally get a chance to go toe-to-toe with their crosstown rival the Purple Diamonds after losing to them at the beginning of the season. Meanwhile, Miss D challenges head captain, Kayla, to take the reins and run practice as the team prepares for their high stakes rematch and Coach Traci from the YCDT Supastarz of Miami makes a surprise appearance at the competition.

10.title: Miss D Breaks It Down
10.plot: Miss D will share some secrets and give us the history of hip hop majorettes...we'll get dish from the moms and girls on behind-the-scenes drama from the first nine episodes as well as performances by the Dancing Dolls, Baby Dolls, moms, and even Sunjai's dad JJ! Producers also plan to surprise Miss D and the girls with special celebrity shout-outs and guest appearances. This one-hour special will be hosted by Kim Coles.

11.title: Behind the Battles
11.plot: This episode of Bring It! features a unique look at some of the most memorable performances and defining moments from the past season. Brand new interviews and never-before-seen footage provide a fresh perspective on the lives of Miss D, the dancers, their families and their rivals, giving viewers an even greater understanding of just what it takes to be a Dancing Doll!

12.title: So You Wanna Be a Doll?
12.plot: Includes extended dance footage not seen in original episode. The new competition season begins next week, and Miss D is building up a new team with her annual team tryouts, where even veteran dancers must compete again for a spot on the squad. Scores of Dancing Doll hopefuls descend on the Dollhouse Dance Factory for the Dancing Dolls team tryouts. Will Sunjai return to tryout for the team? Veteran Doll Tamia challenges Camryn for the coveted "head co-captain" position and Crystianna battles her nerves as she attempts to perform her very first solo.

13.title: Prom or Competition?
13.plot: The Dancing Dolls go toe-to-toe with their rivals to score the Grand Championship title at the Bay Area Battle in Memphis, TN. Many dancers and their Moms, however, fear a risky strategy by Miss D will cost them the win. And Sunjai is forced to choose between performing with her squad or attending her high school prom.

14.title: A New Rival Emerges
14.plot: The Dancing Dolls are forced to defend their home turf when a cocky new dance team from Miami, Florida travels all the way to Jackson to challenge them. Meanwhile, Miss D enlists the Dancing Doll Parents to help spice up the team's Beyonce -inspired creative dance and the tables are turned when Sunjai's mom, Selena, finds herself at risk of getting cut from the routine.

15.title: Kayla's Big Surprise
15.plot: The Dancing Dolls face-off against rivals in Jackson, MS. Miss D decides to attempt the team's first-ever lyrical routine, but dancers struggle with the choreography. And Kayla gets a surprise from the team that she'll never forget for her high school prom.

16.title: Nashville Smackdown
16.plot: The Dancing Dolls travel to Nashville, TN to take on squads from all over the South at one of the biggest competitions they've ever attended. The Moms hatch a master plan to spy on Miss D in the dance studio and decide to hold a bake sale to fund their scheme. And Kayla makes a decision that leads Miss D and the team to call her leadership into question.

17.title: Baby Dolls vs. Baby Tigerettes
17.plot: Miss D shows the Baby Dancing Dolls some tough love as she prepares them to take center stage and battle their number one rival, the Baby Prancing Tigerettes. Meanwhile, the Dancing Doll Parents get the chance to perform a full routine at competition and Rittany, Crystianna's Aunt, struggles to keep up with the rest of the squad.

18.title: Pray for Sunjai
18.plot: Kayla comes to Sunjai's aid as she struggles to finally make the stand battle squad before time runs out and the competition season comes to an end. Meanwhile, the Dancing Dolls must defend their home turf when Mississippi rival, Virtuous Divine, returns to Jackson looking for payback after a recent defeat.

19.title: Dolls vs. Dollz: The Rematch
19.plot: The Dancing Dolls head to Memphis, TN to settle some unfinished business with rival squad, the Dynamic Diamond Dollz. Meanwhile, Camryn's dream of becoming head-captain is in jeopardy when she has difficulty learning a new routine. The Dolls also go toe-to-toe with an all-male dance team in a Hip Hop competition.

20.title: Bucking for Revenge
20.plot: After settling for a tie in stand battle last week versus the Dynamic Diamond Dollz, the Dancing Dolls are ready for a rematch. But first they'll have to contend with the largest field of competitors they've faced all season! Meanwhile, Miss D takes a risky gamble on the Baby Dancing Dolls and the race to replace Kayla as head captain next year heats up as Camryn and Tamia begin to bump heads.

21.title: Chumps or Champions?
21.plot: After a winning competition season, the Dancing Dolls must face off against their two biggest rivals, the Prancing Tigerettes and the Divas of Olive Branch, in order to finally reclaim the title of "Top Majorette Dance Team in the South." However, a talented new squad emerges and threatens the Dolls' plans to avenge last season's loss to the Divas in "Battle Royale." Meanwhile, Miss D must step up and take the dance floor herself to help secure the championship for the team.

22.title: The DD4L Tour
22.plot: In a special two-hour episode of BRING IT!, Miss D and the Dancing Dolls hit the road on a mission to bring their exciting majorette style of dance to young girls all across the country. But when faced with Miss Dianna's aggressive coaching style, will these aspiring dancers "buck or cry"? Meanwhile, in a surprising twist, teammates Kayla, Camryn, Crystianna and Sunjai are pitted against each other in stand battle for the very first time, causing things to get heated as they compete for a special featured role in the upcoming competition season.

1.title: Miami Heat Is Back
1.plot: Take a look back at the greatest rivals the Dancing Dolls have ever faced and reflect on the incredible highs and lows the moms and their daughters have experienced with exclusive never before seen footage. We will also take a sneak peek into what's in store for the next season on the Dancing Dolls Tour in Dianna's quest to become the best Majorette team in America.

2.title: Miss D Loses Her Cool
2.plot: Tensions run high as the Dancing Dolls go head-to-head with archrival, the Divas of Olive Branch, for the very first time since losing to them in last season's Battle Royale. Miss D hires male choreographers to give her girls an aggressive edge in the Hip Hop Trio category while Selena and new mom, Tawantza, bond over their shared love of "being beautiful." Then, at competition, a verbal confrontation between Miss D and the Divas' Coach Neva leads one of them to make a surprising decision!

3.title: Hometown Showdown
3.plot: The Dancing Dolls face-off against fierce cross-town rival, the Purple Diamonds, for the very first time since a controversial competition last season. Dianna reveals a surprising secret weapon that tests the dancers like never before and the Moms confront Miss D after a risky decision causes them to fear for the girls' safety.

4.title: Bucking in Bama
4.plot: The Dancing Dolls head deep into uncharted territory when they attend a competition in Mobile, Alabama. Camryn takes the reigns as Head Captain for the week and struggles as she attempts to lead stand battle for the very first time. Meanwhile, Rittany considers taking her niece to join a rival dance squad after she and Dianna clash over Crystianna cheerleading.

5.title: Selena's Triple Threat
5.plot: Everything is on the line this week as Dianna decides to take a risk and put new dancers on the front lines against returning rival team, Infamous Dancerettes, who have been sharpening their skills and are ready to take on the Dolls.

6.title: No Stopping Kayla
6.plot: The Dancing Dolls head deep into enemy territory to challenge Mobile, Alabama's number one dance squad, the Diamondettes, on their own home turf. Meanwhile, Miss D confronts Kayla about her recent weight gain as she prepares for a high stakes solo performance and Star, Sky and ZaTia try their best to crush it in their very first Field Show.

7.title: Stamp Out Atlanta
7.plot: After losing twice in a row to their hometown rivals, the Purple Diamonds, the pressure is on for the Dancing Dolls to take home a first place trophy this week, or risk losing their reputation as the best majorette dance squad in Jackson, MS. Meanwhile, Camryn struggles after Miss D taps her to represent the team in the solo category and Tawantza pressures her daughter ZaTia to step up her game after Dianna cuts her from creative dance yet again.

8.title: Traci's Revenge
8.plot: Coach Traci and the YCDT Supastarz return to Mississippi looking for revenge after losing to Dianna and the Dolls the last time they battled. Meanwhile, Miss D steps up her game and creates one of the most elaborate routines she has ever choreographed, and Selena raises hell after Dianna cuts her twin daughters, Star and Sky

9.title: Captain Down
9.plot: The Dancing Dolls travel back to Atlanta, Georgia, for a much anticipated rematch against hometown favorites, the Dazzling Divas. Meanwhile, Selena butts heads with Miss D after Sunjai fails to make cuts in creative dance and a freak injury threatens to keep captain Kayla from performing, leaving the Dolls at a major disadvantage.

10.title: Don't Do it Neva
10.plot: Still angry over Miss D's Drag Queen Diva stand, Neva crosses the line in Stand Battle this week and it could cost both teams dearly. State testing forces Miss D to make a risky decision and Tina goes on the offense when a new coach threatens to sideline Kayla.

11.title: Baby Tiger Attack
11.plot: As the Baby Dancing Dolls attempt to defeat their biggest rival, the Baby Prancing Tigerettes, for the first time ever, Tigerette coach Quincy causes a stir when he reveals some controversial choreography. Meanwhile, Tina and Mimi butt heads with the Baby Dancing Doll Moms and Tawantza secretly tries to play the conflict to her advantage by positioning herself as a mentor to the next generation of Dancing Doll Parents.

12.title: Copycat
12.plot: Coming off a surprising loss to Coach Quincy and the Baby Prancing Tigerettes in the Battle of the Babies, Miss D is out for retribution this week when the Big Dolls go head-to-head with the Tigerettes. Meanwhile, only one of Selena's twin daughters manages to make cuts for the team's 80's-inspired creative dance routine and Dianna accuses Quincy of stealing her choreography.

13.title: Road to Royale
13.plot: Miss D and the Dancing Dolls finally get a chance to go toe-to-toe with their crosstown rival the Purple Diamonds after losing to them at the beginning of the season. Meanwhile, Miss D challenges head captain, Kayla, to take the reins and run practice as the team prepares for their high stakes rematch and Coach Traci from the YCDT Supastarz of Miami makes a surprise appearance at the competition.

14.title: Battle Royale 2015
14.plot: Miss D and the Dancing Dolls face off against their three biggest rivals, Purple Diamonds, YCDT Supastarz of Miami and the Divas of Olive Branch, in the final and most anticipated competition of the season, the Battle Royale. Meanwhile, the girls get a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to audition for a full scholarship to the prestigious dance program at DeSales University in Pennsylvania and Dianna surprises the team when she taps Dancing Doll parents, Tina and Mimi, to be the secret weapon for the week. (Includes additional footage not seen in original episode.)

15.title: Rival Rehash
15.plot: In this special episode of Bring It!, exclusive uncut stand battles from this year's Battle Royale, as well as a special extended version of this past season's most explosive face-off with the Dolls' arch nemesis, the Divas of Olive Branch, help provide a new perspective on the Dancing Dolls' fiercest rivalries. The Baby Dancing Dolls growing competition is also explored in a never-before-seen stand battle versus a strong squad all the way from Cincinnati, Ohio, and the results of the Dancing Dolls' recent auditions to receive scholarships to the DeSales University ...

16.title: A Whole New Doll Game
16.plot: The summer season is here and things are heating up in the Dollhouse! Miss Dianna is shaking things up in the studio, throwing the team and the Dancing Doll Parents into frenzy. The Captain spot is up-for-grabs and Miss D announces that the top contenders must compete in weekly dance-offs to determine the Captain, making tensions run high.

17.title: Dancing Dolls NOT for Life
17.plot: The heat of the summer season reaches a boiling point when Tawantza's temper flares out-of-control. Will a confrontation with Dianna lead to Zatia and Tawantza getting the boot?

18.title: Selena's Makeover Madness
18.plot: The Dancing Dolls are under extra pressure this week after two straight losses and a double elimination this week in stand battle. Dianna enlists the help of Assistant Coach Kayla to help choreograph a hip-hop routine.

19.title: The Big Apple and the Bitter Apple
19.plot: Coach D has a big surprise for the Dolls--twelve girls have been selected to go on a field trip to New York City!

20.title: Saturday Night Fights
20.plot: Coach D takes the Dancing Dolls out of their comfort zone and onto a football field for a spectacular Saturday Night Lights field show and stand battle competition. However, the girls struggle with learning their routines with a full marching band and severe weather looming.

21.title: Who You Callin' Cookie?
21.plot: New teams are traveling far and wide to take on the Dancing Dolls and Miss D is feeling the pressure. During practice, Dianna yells at the girls more than usual, forcing the DDP moms to take matters into their own hands and confront Miss D in an intervention to address her coaching style.

22.title: Pom Pom Panic
22.plot: Pom-poms are flying this week as Dianna coaches the girls through a Southern stand-off. New coaches stoop to all-time lows but Dianna must shake it off and stay on course for a grueling competition in three different categories. Meanwhile, we see a softer side of Miss D as she renews her wedding vows to husband, Robert.

23.title: Tick, Tick, Boom!
23.plot: With the Summer Slam Dance Championship only week away, the girls feel extra pressure to show off their talents and prove to Miss D that they have what it takes to be captain of the team next season. Emotions are running high in the Dollhouse as Kayla and Sunjai graduate from High School.

24.title: Summer Slam
24.plot: It is tense in the Dollhouse -- after a season of competing for the captain position, Dianna will finally name the team's next leader. Later, the Dancing Dolls face their fiercest rivals and the girls will attempt to knock out their opponents to win the championship title and a $5,000 prize. Plus, get ready to Step It Up!

1.title: Straight Outta Jackson
1.plot: New Doll. New Drama. Coach D is more determined than ever to lead her Dolls to victory in this week's Street Battle against Compton.

2.title: The Bucking Ballerina
2.plot: Recovering from the Street Battle, Dianna is struggling to get her new team into shape. Crystianna and Faith vie for a solo while new mom Dana makes waves in the viewing room.

3.title: Hell Week
3.plot: Coach D has a show stopping idea for this week's competition, but an unexpected wrench puts the Dolls' participation at risk.

4.title: Homecoming Hell
4.plot: Dianna and the Dolls have their work cut out for them with a competition, homecoming parade and a halftime show on their plates, all while preparing to face one of their most formidable rivals.

5.title: Rittany's Revolt
5.plot: This week Dianna prepares the Dolls to face some of their toughest competitors of the season, but Rittany throws a wrench in the plan when she hears that the team is participating in another parade.

6.title: The Wicked Witch of Jackson
6.plot: It's "Fright Night in the Dollhouse" as the Dolls are competing on Halloween and Dianna has big plans for a spooky, show-stopping routine. But fierce rivals, The Purple Diamonds, await the Dolls at the competition

7.title: Bucking Bride
7.plot: Church bells are ringing in the Dollhouse as Dianna prepares an ambitious Gospel duet with an unlikely pair.

8.title: Blow It Up
8.plot: There are more jeers than cheers this week as the Dolls rehearse for a pom-pom competition against their Texas rivals, Xplosive, and the new girls struggle to catch on.

9.title: Flash Mob Madness
9.plot: The Dancing Dolls are under extra pressure this week after two straight losses and a double elimination this week in stand battle. Dianna enlists the help of Assistant Coach Kayla to help choreograph a hip-hop routine.

10.title: Three Strikes, You're Out
10.plot: The Dollhouse goes retro as Dianna choreographs a '90s-inspired TLC-themed dance, but when an unlikely Doll is cast in a leading role, Dianna struggles to get the team in shape in time.

11.title: Neva Gets Even
11.plot: Still angry over Miss D�۪s Drag Queen Diva stand, Neva crosses the line in Stand Battle this week and it could cost both teams dearly. State testing forces Miss D to make a risky decision and Tina goes on the offense when a new coach threatens to sideline Kayla.

12.title: They're Coming for Us!
12.plot: The road to the Battle Royale is more treacherous-than-ever as semifinals force the Dancing Dolls take on 8 of their fiercest rivals to secure a spot.

13.title: Face the Music! It's the Finale!
13.plot: It's time to face the music at the Battle Royale! After losing two years in a row, Dianna overloads her team with complicated choreography and ambitious stands that involve guest appearances from alumni.

14.title: Spilling the Tea Reunion Special
14.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

15.title: Team Kayla vs. Team Dianna
15.plot: David vs. Goliath, as Team Kayla goes against Team Dianna in an effort to get new dancers trained for the summer dance season.

16.title: The Return of Neva the Diva
16.plot: Coach D enlists the Dancing Dolls in a grudge match with her most bitter rival, Neva-the-Diva, from the Divas of Olive Branch. Dianna will stop at nothing to beat her arch-nemesis.

17.title: Compton Call Out
17.plot: There is both "bucking" and "crumping" in the house this week. Coach D accepts a rematch from the Divas of Compton, which quickly turns into the ultimate grudge match. The Free-style category causes a FRENZY in the viewing room when Coach D decides to shake things up, causing one DDP to lose all control. Meanwhile, Mimi struggles with letting Camryn begin dating. Can Dianna toughen up her team in time to defeat the west coast scrappers?

18.title: Ratchcity!
18.plot: Be prepared: it's the most EXPLOSIVE competition in Dancing Doll history yet! After a series of losses in the freestyle category, Coach D decides to whip her team into shape in an effort to prepare the girls for a 6-way showdown.

19.title: Hoop Dreams Drama
19.plot: Coach D is "ballin" in the Dollhouse this week, as she takes her game to the next level and enlists her husband to help with an ambitious basketball-themed creative routine.

20.title: Scholarship Dreams and Dating Nightmares
20.plot: It's "back-to-school" for Coach D this week as the as the dancers compete for a coveted scholarship at a local university and a spot on their elite dance squad.

21.title: Dancing with the Enemy
21.plot: This week, enemies become allies as the Dancing Dolls team up with notorious hometown rivals, the Purple Diamonds, to take on Memphis in a city vs. city competition.

23.title: Wigging Out
23.plot: Coach D's big plans backfire when her decision to include 30 new dancers in a football field competition puts the team in serious jeopardy for game day.

24.title: Lil Niqo and a Lot of Sweat
24.plot: This week is the final competition before the Summer Dance Slam and Coach D turns up the heat.

25.title: Stomp! Summer Slam Shocker
25.plot: Coach D tries her hand at a spectacular stepping routine for the ultimate competition--the Summer Dance Slam.

1.title: Episode #4.1
1.plot: Bring It!'s back for a brand new season and for their first competition, Coach D goes up against her arch rival Neva the Diva in a New Orleans dance battle.

2.title: Diana Said Knock You Out
2.plot: The Dancing Dolls are stepping into the ring with a boxing-themed routine against unknown rivals Black Ice, and find their opponents really pack a punch.

3.title: Coach D Meets Queen B
3.plot: Coach D needs her Dancing Dolls to slay the competition after the results from the last competition.

4.title: Bringing It to the Big Apple
4.plot: Coach D has a big surprise for the Dolls--twelve girls have been selected to go on a field trip to New York City!

7.title: Attack of the B Squad
7.plot: Miss D heads to Birmingham to prep the newest Dolls to battle their big sisters of Jackson.

8.title: Attack of the B Squad
8.plot: Miss D adds a twist for the Dancing Dolls' stand battle. The veterans are benched.

9.title: Episode #4.9
9.plot: The Dancing Dolls and Miss D face Black Ice from Ohio. Can the Dolls succeed?

10.title: Revenge of the Robo Dolls
10.plot: Miss D and the Dolls face arch rivals the Prancing Tigerettes.

11.title: Cookie Bites Back
11.plot: The Dancing Dolls get the shock of the season when they find out that Coach D's swapped studios with Tyrus, the flamboyant coach of the Elite Stars.

12.title: La La Land
12.plot: Coach D and the Dolls take on Los Angeles for a grudge match against Compton. One doll gets the opportunity of a lifetime while the team learns Coach D's Smurf creative.

13.title: Lemons to "Lemonade?"
13.plot: Dancing Dolls face their hometown rivals, the Purple Diamonds so Coach D goes all out with a Beyonc -inspired creative that has the girls attempting to perform in a pool.

14.title: Battle for Broadway
14.plot: The Broadway Dance Center comes to Jackson to pick one Dancing Doll for their summer intensive scholarship.

15.title: Deliver us from Neva
15.plot: With Battle Royale looming next week, Coach D holds tryouts for a very special solo role and Rittany's gunning for Crystianna to get it, by any means necessary.

16.title: Battle Royale: Up in Flames!
16.plot: It's the Battle Royale, and Dianna's concocted her most ambitious creative dance yet, a spectacular Willy Wonka-inspired routine.

17.title: Crossing the Line
17.plot: As a brand new dance season begins, Coach D has decided to shake-up EVERYTHING familiar in the Dollhouse. The DDPs get a rude awakening when they find out their antics have them permanently exiled from the viewing room. Meanwhile, new faces are causing a commotion in the Dollhouse and Chrystianna stirring-up trouble in enemy territory.

18.title: Rumble in the Jungle
18.plot: When a Dollhouse heavy-hitter gets injured, a new DDP tries to sweet talk her way up the Dollhouse ladder. Rittany questions her decision to defect from the team. Also, when Dianna puts the heat on her new Baby Doll team, a Baby Mama mutiny erupts.

19.title: #Clapback
19.plot: After defecting to Divas of Olive Branch, a regretful Rittany tries to woo Coach D into letting Crystianna back on the team.

20.title: Battle for Oz
20.plot: Broadway singer and international star, Todrick Hall, surprises the Dolls with a "Oz" inspired choreography challenge that pits Dolls against Dolls. When the competition heats up, tears are shed, and tempers flare in effort to win the performance opportunity of a lifetime.

21.title: A Very Bring It! Holiday
21.plot: It's a holiday extravaganza. Coach D, the Dancing Dolls and the DDP celebrate the holidays with sizzling sneak peaks of the season, answering viewer questions, and celebrating super fans who are heroes in their communities.

22.title: Secrets, Lies, and Slumber Parties
22.plot: Dianna announces that she will be taking only 5 Dancing Dolls at the end of the dance season to a National Competition.

23.title: Coach D Resigns
23.plot: Coach D's frustration with the Dancing Dolls' lackluster attitudes results in dramatic departure from the Dollhouse.

24.title: Stand Battle Shake-Up
24.plot: Dianna has a HUGE surprise set for this week's Stand Battle- the DDPs will be a mandatory part of Stand Battle.

25.title: Doll Meets World
25.plot: In the last creative dance competition of the season, Dianna takes a big risk placing untried girls front and center in an elaborate "around the world" creative routine.

26.title: The Dolls' Last Chance
26.plot: Coach D enlists celebrity choreographers to train, audition, and select five girls for the National Competition in Philadelphia. It's any Doll's game as they struggle through intense routines in many genres. A nervous Kayla scrambles to prepare her newly formed dance team for their first hip hop competition that could make or break her dreams to be a dance coach.

27.title: National Pressure
27.plot: It's GAME TIME in the Dollhouse. After months of intense training Coach D and the Dancing Dolls will head to Philadelphia for an epic competition with a multitude of dance genres.

1.title: If You Can't Stand the Heat...
1.plot: Coach D begins a new dance season with the ultimate quest to find the Dancing Dolls' next captain. A new dancer and DDP shakes up the team after moving from NYC to Jackson, and introducing some "high maintenance" demands. Will a new captain nominee step up to a Wild-West themed "showdown"? Or will the competition leave the Dancing Dolls in the dust?

2.title: The Sister Showdown
2.plot: The Dollhouse takes "sibling rivalry" to the next-level when the Dollhouse "captain nominee" must stand off against her sister, who just happens to be the captain of Jackson's hometown enemy, the Purple Diamonds.

3.title: Let's Talk About Texts, Bby
3.plot: The Dancing Dolls are preparing for an epic school-spirit competition, but the practices are interrupted when a texting scandal rocks the team. Coach D's punishment for the Dolls involved puts several of the potential captains' futures on the line.

7.title: Stands and Deliver
7.plot: The Dolls face off against their biggest foes, The Prancing Tigerettes and Divas of Olive Branch, in a heated Stands in Stands battle with a live band. Dianna finally takes Crystianna off probation and puts her to the test leading floor stands, but Crystianna fails to impress during practice. Meanwhile, a desperate Selena enlists the help of the DDP to convince Dianna to let her and the twins back in the Dollhouse.

8.title: Dance for Your Rights
8.plot: Coach D creates a female empowerment routine that she believes will rock the dance floor. But when she gets carried away, her routine quickly spirals into a 28-minute dance marathon that exhausts the team and her lead Dancing Doll. Will the dancers overcome fatigue and confusion on the floor, or will the routine crash and burn? Meanwhile a few paranoid DDPs suspect Jaylene is being secretly groomed for the captain position and investigate.

10.title: Grudge Match Gone Wrong
10.plot: All bets are off as the Dancing Dolls face off against their most formidable foe, Black Ice, in an epic grudge match! But when the team's "secret weapon" backfires, the Dolls are left without a plan of attack. Will the team find a new strategy to bring to the battle? Later, an emergency situation sends the competition into chaos.

11.title: There's a Crowd
11.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

12.title: The Ultimate Captain's Battle
12.plot: Coach D narrows down the search for the new captain to the final two and challenges them to face off in a heated Doll vs. Doll competition to determine who will be named the next captain! But when Coach D lashes out at both captain potentials for not leading their teams, emotions explode and the tears flow!

imdb.plot outline: Bring It! is a new dance reality show which focuses on the dance team, The Dancing Dolls, from Mississippi. They are a competition dance team, and their style is, "Hip-Hop Majorettes." This show is produced by Lifetime, and is lively, and the girls are fun to watch. Coach D is a strong woman, with a no-nonsense personality, and drives the girls under her to be the best they can be. Still, she has a human side, and she does care about the girls, and tries to be supportive of them (something we don't see too often in another, well-known dance reality show). Further, the "drama" of the dance moms is surprisingly low-key when compared to another reality dance show, also produced by Lifetime. Give this show a chance. It will surprise you, as the dancing is different from what you are likely used to watching.
